g.text: BodypartObject Header Attributes Attributes defined by the Part interface only. Attributes include a second Content - Type attribute. A Multipart Message can hold more than one Bodypart object. Multipart Object Content Body The content body itself can be either a DataHandler object containing data, or another Multipart object. Bodypart Object
Header Attributes Normal Message, includes a Content- Type attribute set to ‘ Multipart ’. Message Content Body Normal Message, includes a Content body of type ‘ Multipart ’.

A multipart message is a simple message object where the Content- Type is set to ‘multipart,’ and the Content Body carries a reference to a Multipart object. A Multipart object is a container of Bodypart objects, where each Bodypart can contain either a DataHandler or another Multipart object.
